Let $f : ZZ times ZZ -> RR$ be a function which satisfies $f(0, 0) = 1$ and

$ f(m, n) + f(m + 1, n) + f(m, n + 1) + f(m + 1, n + 1) = 0 $

for all $m, n in ZZ$ (where $ZZ$ and $RR$ denote the set of all integers and
all real numbers, respectively). Prove that $|f(m, n)| >= 1/3$, for infinitely
many pairs of integers $(m, n)$.
